---
description: Style-scope guard — color/typography only unless explicitly requested
globs:
  - "src/**/*.{svelte,css,scss}"
alwaysApply: true
---

When a task mentions color/visual tweaks, DO NOT change layout or stacking.
- Allowed without explicit permission: color, background-color, fill, stroke, border-color, text-decoration, outline-color, box-shadow color, font-family/size/weight/line-height/letter/word spacing.
- Tailwind: only classes affecting color/typography (text-*, bg-*, fill-*, stroke-*, border-*, decoration-*, accent-*, placeholder-*, ring-*, shadow-*). Do not add or remove z-*, position, display, flex-*, grid-*, gap-*, inset-*, top/right/bottom/left, order-*, overflow-*, transform/translate/scale/rotate, opacity, pointer-events, isolation.

Never modify:
- z-index or classes starting with `z-`
- position/display/flow (position, display, float, clear)
- spacing/layout (margin, padding, width, height) unless explicitly requested
- transforms/filters or stacking/isolation/perspective

If the requested change cannot be done without touching the above, STOP and ask for approval. Always output a unified diff and include a short **Change Scope** list at the end (properties touched).
